default&#xa0; 
defaultSeveral Police and Crime Commissioners are 
defaultcollaborating with U
defaultniversities 
defaulton
default 
defaultevidence-based research 
defaulton local crime and disorder. Police and Crime Commissioner for Northamptonshire is establishing a ‘Police, Crime and Justice Institute’ within a University to bring together research activity and practical translation of research evidence 
defaultwith the aim of
default enha
defaultncing
default problem solving. In South Wales, the Universities P
defaultolice Science Institute (UPSI) is a
defaultn
default innovative partnership 
defaultbetween Cardiff University’s Viol
defaultence and Society Research Group
default and South Wales Police, 
defaultand is supported by the South Wales Commissioner wit
defaulth funding of £1.2 million over five
default years.
default The collaboration focuses upon community engagement, intelligence and neighbourhood policing, countering violent extremism and police innovation and reform. 
